articles.title: Simone McGurk wants decades old WA abortion laws 'brought up to scratch' - ABC News
articles.description: WA Women's Interests Minister Simone McGurk makes some of her strongest comments on abortion reform to date, declaring some of the responsibility rests with the federal government to make the services available and affordable for Australian women.
articles.content:
WA's decades-old abortion laws need to be brought "up to scratch", according to the state's Women's Interests Minister.
